  {
    "client_msg_id": "e77aa22d-3364-4921-91de-49335b0263c0",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "I was also a bit puzzled to find that the \"live coding\" community is mostly performance art related at the moment...\n\nThe \"debugging programs without restarting them\" community tends to use terms like \"interactive programming\" or \"REPL-driven programming\".\n\nOf course, all of these things are \"live\" and \"interactive\" in different ways, so there's naturally going to be some overlap. Events like the LIVE workshop tend to feature work from both camps.",
    "user": "UML4ZEKDK",
    "ts": "1670470708.999549",
    "blocks": [
      {
        "type": "rich_text",
        "block_id": "/J3j",
